Citizen videos show the aftermath of the 5.1 and 4.5 earthquake which struck
the city of Lorca in the region of Murcia, Spain on May 11th. According to the
City Council, between 20 000 and 30 000 people slept on the streets, while
brigades check buildings for safety.

[![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2011/05/5713206060_3b5a20a4d5.jpg)](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2011/05/5713206060_3b5a20a4d5.jpg)  
[Terremoto
Lorca](http://www.flickr.com/photos/aperiago/5713206060/in/photostream/) by
[Antonio Periago](http://www.flickr.com/photos/aperiago/) [CC By-
SA](http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/)

The rubble on the streets, the presence of ambulances, casualties and the
damage done to buildings is visible on this
[video](http://youtu.be/mQFcwaHnEq0) mashup. Warning, some images are graphic:

http://youtu.be/mQFcwaHnEq0

On [this one](http://youtu.be/M8_u1akeSd8), a walk around the streets captures
not only images but also background noise:

